@startuml agent_components
title HealthAI - Agents & the LLM Service Seam

interface LLMClient {
  +complete(system, messages, max_tokens, temperature) : LLMResponse
  +is_ai : bool
}

class AnthropicClient
class LocalHeuristicClient
class MockClaudeClient

LLMClient <|.. AnthropicClient
LLMClient <|.. LocalHeuristicClient
LLMClient <|.. MockClaudeClient

class "factory.get_llm_client()" as Factory
Factory --> LLMClient : selects backend\n(env / API key)

class MedicalExtractionAgent
class GuidelineReviewAgent
class AppealGenerationAgent
class ClaudeEvidenceExtractor

MedicalExtractionAgent --> LLMClient
GuidelineReviewAgent --> LLMClient
AppealGenerationAgent --> LLMClient
ClaudeEvidenceExtractor --> LLMClient

class ClinicalReviewEngine
class AppealLetterBuilder
class EvidenceExtractor

GuidelineReviewAgent ..> ClinicalReviewEngine : fallback (offline/fail)
AppealGenerationAgent ..> AppealLetterBuilder : fallback / letter render
ClaudeEvidenceExtractor ..> EvidenceExtractor : fallback (offline/invalid)

note bottom
  Every AI agent has a deterministic fallback so the
  app + tests run with no API key. Output contracts
  (PatientCase / ReviewResult / AppealLetter /
  EvidenceReference) are identical either way.
  ClaudeEvidenceExtractor adds an anti-fabrication
  gate: a quote must appear verbatim in the source.
end note

@enduml
